trans-unit.source: A type that represents the type of redirection.
Gets a <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Channels.RedirectionType"></xref> that represents the cache redirection type.
A cache redirection indicates that the response from a previous request should be used.
This corresponds with the HTTP status code 304 (Not Modified)
The cache redirection type.
Creates a new instance of the <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Channels.RedirectionType"></xref> class with the specified redirection type and redirection namespace.
The redirection type.
The redirection namespace.
A redirection type.
Determines whether the specified object is equal to the current <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Channels.RedirectionType"></xref> instance.
The object to compare to the current <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Channels.RedirectionType"></xref> instance.
`true` if the specified object is equal to the current <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Channels.RedirectionType"></xref>; otherwise, `false`.
Gets the hash code for this instance.
A 32-bit signed integer hash code.
Gets the namespace of the <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Channels.RedirectionType"></xref>.
The namespace of the redirection type.
Returns a value that indicates whether two instances of the <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Channels.RedirectionType"></xref> types are equal.
A <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Channels.RedirectionType"></xref> instance.
A <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Channels.RedirectionType"></xref> instance.
`true` if the values of left and right are equal; otherwise, `false`.
Returns a value that indicates whether two instances of the <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Channels.RedirectionType"></xref> types are not equal.
A <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Channels.RedirectionType"></xref> instance.
A <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Channels.RedirectionType"></xref> instance.
`true` if the values of left and right are not equal; otherwise, `false`.
Gets a <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Channels.RedirectionType"></xref> that represents the resource redirection type.
A resource redirection indicates the requested resource has been relocated to the specified location(s).

If one location is specified, then this maps to HTTP status code 301 (Moved Permanently) or 307 (Temporary Redirect), depending on the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.RedirectionDuration> selected.
If multiple locations are provided, then this maps to the 300 (Multiple Choices) HTTP status code.
This is the default value for <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.RedirectionType>.
The resource redirection type.
Converts the current <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Channels.RedirectionType"></xref> to its equivalent string representation.
A string representation of the value of the current <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Channels.RedirectionType"></xref> object.
Gets a <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Channels.RedirectionType"></xref> that represents the use intermediary redirection type.
A use intermediary redirection indicates the requested resource must be accessed through an intermediate service, for example, an HTTP proxy server.
This corresponds to the HTTP status code 305 (Use Proxy)
The resource redirection type.
Gets the value of the <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Channels.RedirectionType"></xref>.
The value of the redirection type.
